{"type":"message","id":"f9d3fc70","parentId":"715b1e97","timestamp":"2026-06-06T13:03:38.322Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still WrongRequestBody. Let me look at the API docs more carefully. The issue might be with the field type or the property format for update.\n\nLooking at the tool description again:\n```\nActions: create（创建字段）, list（列出所有字段）, update（更新字段，支持只传 field_name 改名）, delete（删除字段）。\n```\n\nFor update, it says \"支持只传 field_name 改名\" - so update can rename by passing field_name. But the property format for updating options might need to be different.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe the issue is that SingleSelect fields with options can't be updated via the field update API, or maybe the format is different.\n\nLet me try creating a new field and deleting the old one instead. Or maybe I should use the batch_update or something.\n\nActually, looking at the error more carefully - \"WrongRequestBody\" means the request body format is wrong. Let me check if there's a specific format needed for updating SingleSelect options.\n\nActually, maybe the problem is that I can't update the options of a SingleSelect field via the API - it might require deleting and recreating the field. Or maybe the property needs to include more fields.\n\nLet me try just renaming first to see if update works at all.\n","thinkingSignature":"0668c02894dfc14323cb5c6af80e918182a6e3ecfa8a1ed9504373870e82337b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e3edc5f5d4124a9896ed693d","name":"feishu_bitable_app_table_field","arguments":{"action":"update","app_token":"AKppbA…QnZd","table_id":"tblHU2do30jzinJT","field_name":"推荐等级","field_id":"fldama07y5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":638,"output":361,"cacheRead":126005,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":127004,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780751010923,"responseId":"06734da39b96c