{"type":"message","id":"2b4a143b","parentId":"fac75bd2","timestamp":"2026-06-06T13:03:47.245Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"DataNotChange error - that's weird, it means no change? But I'm not passing any property changes. Let me try with just the field_name and see if that's even a valid update.\n\nActually \"DataNotChange\" might mean the field name is already that value. So the rename to same name doesn't change anything.\n\nThe issue is that I can't update the options of a SingleSelect field through the update API. This is a known limitation of the Feishu API - you typically can't modify the options of a SingleSelect field after creation, you'd need to delete and recreate the field.\n\nLet me try a different approach - delete the problematic fields and recreate them with the correct options. But I need to be careful because there might be data in those fields.\n\nActually, let me check if the feishu_bitable_app_table_field supports delete and create.\n","thinkingSignature":"d8c8aa15e749fcaaaef90c23b53a0b83cdfcf76bcd4b748f65997c44d893d192"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n选项更新不了，飞书限制 SingleSelect 选项修改。\n\n两个方案：\n\n**方案1：删掉重建**（会丢失已有数据）\n删除 推荐等级 和 站点 字段，重新创建干净的选项\n\n**方案2：跳过**  \n不改选项了，保持现状，以后新建记录时用正确的选项\n\n你想用哪个？如果选品库里已有数据不多，我建议方案1重新建。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":388,"output":253,"cacheRead":126642,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":127283,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780751020185,"responseId":"06734dacf342ecdb4104e18fb4f054cb"}}
